WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.460 --> 00:00:08.960
Behold the works
of Rhaenyra Targaryen!

2
00:00:09.340 --> 00:00:10.629
It's a lie.

3
00:00:10.630 --> 00:00:11.800
Having lost my own son.

4
00:00:11.920 --> 00:00:13.630
that I would inflict
such a thing.

5
00:00:14.510 --> 00:00:17.350
We will pay the Princess
back in her own bloody coin.

6
00:00:17.930 --> 00:00:20.020
Go to Dragonstone
and strike down Rhaenyra

7
00:00:20.180 --> 00:00:21.180
in her own halls.

8
00:00:21.181 --> 00:00:22.519
You would send me to my death?

9
00:00:22.520 --> 00:00:25.020
Or to triumph and glory.

10
00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:26.349
They tell me that you
are the one

11
00:00:26.350 --> 00:00:28.520
that dragged my body
out of the sea.

12
00:00:28.690 --> 00:00:30.940
I am indebted to you. Alyn.

13
00:00:31.650 --> 00:00:33.990
My letters to Rhaenyra.
has there been any answer?

14
00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:36.159
An apology for her dead son?

15
00:00:36.160 --> 00:00:37.199
None. Your Grace.

16
00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:38.829
We must presume that
the Princess

17
00:00:38.830 --> 00:00:40.289
has refused the offered terms.

18
00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:42.540
And that war is now inevitable.

19
00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:46.709
You struck down a child.

20
00:00:46.710 --> 00:00:48.169
It was a mistake.

21
00:00:48.170 --> 00:00:52.710
Do you accept me as your
Queen and ruler?

22
00:00:54.670 --> 00:00:56.010
I cannot trust you. Daemon.

23
00:00:56.180 --> 00:00:57.600
<i>I will fly to Harrenhal</i>

24
00:00:57.680 --> 00:00:59.720
<i>and set our toe hold
in the Riverlands.</i>

25
00:01:01.140 --> 00:01:03.220
Take Moondancer. and keep
a watch on King's Landing.

26
00:01:03.350 --> 00:01:04.520
I will be vigilant.

27
00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:07.730
Who are they?

28
00:01:07.850 --> 00:01:08.859
Rat catchers.

29
00:01:08.860 --> 00:01:09.860
What have you done?

30
00:01:09.861 --> 00:01:10.900
I had them hanged.

31
00:01:11.020 --> 00:01:12.859
The maggot confessed to
an accomplice.

32
00:01:12.860 --> 00:01:14.149
<i>He could not say which man
it was.</i>

33
00:01:14.150 --> 00:01:15.989
<i>Then why curse your name?</i>

34
00:01:15.990 --> 00:01:18.410
Instead of judgement.
you diminish us!

35
00:01:18.530 --> 00:01:20.829
Remove your badge. Ser Otto.

36
00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:22.160
Give it to Cole.

37
00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:29.920
You may go.

38
00:01:30.040 --> 00:01:31.880
Ser Erryk. have someone
take her down.

39
00:01:34.880 --> 00:01:35.880
A moment.

40
00:01:38.760 --> 00:01:40.100
Brother!

41
00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.730
Forgive me.

42
00:03:44.340 --> 00:03:47.639
Aeron Bracken.
worst horseman among us.

43
00:03:49.970 --> 00:03:51.849
Must be my swordsmanship.

44
00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:54.480
- (laughter) - Can you
even get that thing up?

45
00:03:54.980 --> 00:03:56.819
Well enough
for killing Blackwoods.

46
00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:59.030
Bracken!

47
00:04:04.320 --> 00:04:07.370
Put the boundary stones back.

48
00:04:08.370 --> 00:04:09.740
We didn't move them.

49
00:04:09.870 --> 00:04:11.750
Did they move themselves. then?

50
00:04:11.870 --> 00:04:12.870
Just rolled their way over

51
00:04:12.871 --> 00:04:14.669
so Bracken cows
can fill their bellies

52
00:04:14.670 --> 00:04:16.539
- on Blackwood grass?
- The assize at Riverrun...

53
00:04:16.540 --> 00:04:18.210
Fuck the assize...

54
00:04:19.210 --> 00:04:20.710
and fuck you.

55
00:04:21.260 --> 00:04:22.720
This is our land.

56
00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:30.890
It's Bracken land.

57
00:04:34.390 --> 00:04:37.360
- Babe-killer.
- What did you say?

58
00:04:42.070 --> 00:04:45.910
Your false queen.
Rhaenyra. is a kinslayer.

59
00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:50.240
Your uncle declared
for Aegon. did he?

60
00:04:52.950 --> 00:04:56.919
Well then. let me tell you

61
00:04:56.920 --> 00:05:02.419
Aegon Targaryen
is no true king...

62
00:05:02.420 --> 00:05:06.470
just as you are no true knight.

63
00:05:06.930 --> 00:05:11.220
You're both
craven. little cunts!

64
00:05:20.820 --> 00:05:23.569
You wouldn't dare.

65
00:06:04.980 --> 00:06:07.530
He is the basest of villains.

66
00:06:07.990 --> 00:06:10.320
He sullies the
grave of his brother.

67
00:06:12.030 --> 00:06:15.200
I cannot fault him
for keeping his oath.

68
00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:20.670
And what of those who sent him?

69
00:06:41.730 --> 00:06:44.980
Otto Hightower would
never have allowed this.

70
00:06:46.860 --> 00:06:49.570
Hotter blood has
prevailed. I think.

71
00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:52.489
The young men have
taken the bit in their teeth.

72
00:06:52.490 --> 00:06:54.740
They wish to punish. to avenge.

73
00:06:56.540 --> 00:06:58.659
Soon they will not even
remember what it was

74
00:06:58.660 --> 00:07:00.869
that began the war
in the first place.

75
00:07:00.870 --> 00:07:03.540
That is easy enough.
They usurped my throne.

76
00:07:03.710 --> 00:07:05.380
That is one answer.

77
00:07:09.340 --> 00:07:12.220
Or was it when the
child was beheaded?

78
00:07:14.220 --> 00:07:17.060
Or when Aemond killed Luke...

79
00:07:20.060 --> 00:07:23.270
or when Luke took Aemond's eye?

80
00:07:24.060 --> 00:07:27.070
We teeter now at the point
where none of it will matter.

81
00:07:28.230 --> 00:07:30.740
And the desire to kill
and burn takes hold

82
00:07:30.860 --> 00:07:33.070
and reason is forgotten.

83
00:07:34.870 --> 00:07:36.950
There may be another way.

84
00:07:40.540 --> 00:07:42.790
Alicent Hightower.

85
00:07:46.590 --> 00:07:50.550
When last we met. Alicent
said I would make a fine queen.

86
00:07:51.050 --> 00:07:52.470
You've seen what has
happened since then.

87
00:07:52.550 --> 00:07:54.970
She came to me in the hours
after your lord father's death.

88
00:07:55.100 --> 00:07:56.140
She knows war is coming.

89
00:07:56.260 --> 00:07:59.430
and that it'll be savage
beyond all compare.

90
00:08:00.390 --> 00:08:05.559
There is no war so hateful to
the gods as a war between kin.

91
00:08:09.400 --> 00:08:13.320
And no war so bloody
as a war between dragons.

92
00:08:13.450 --> 00:08:17.280
- I do not believe she wants it.
- She sent a raven.

93
00:08:18.790 --> 00:08:20.290
I do not care to
read her message.

94
00:08:20.950 --> 00:08:24.290
- What she did... - It is not her but the
men around her who seek bloodshed.

95
00:08:24.420 --> 00:08:26.290
She permitted it.

96
00:08:27.790 --> 00:08:29.000
As you permitted the murder

97
00:08:29.130 --> 00:08:30.670
of a little boy in his bed.

98
00:08:38.970 --> 00:08:44.100
Alicent is in King's Landing.
Her son sits my throne.

99
00:08:45.850 --> 00:08:48.440
There is nothing
more to be said.

100
00:09:03.160 --> 00:09:05.710
(muffled) Is
all well. lord Hand?

101
00:09:08.130 --> 00:09:10.960
Only they'll be waiting.

102
00:09:51.840 --> 00:09:53.169
There have been tidings in...

103
00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:05.230
Good morrow.
Your Grace. My lords.

104
00:10:13.070 --> 00:10:16.739
- Forgive my lateness.
- Important business. no doubt.

105
00:10:16.740 --> 00:10:18.239
You've appointed new knights

106
00:10:18.240 --> 00:10:20.950
- to the Kingsguard. Your Grace.
- To replace those we lost.

107
00:10:21.070 --> 00:10:24.040
The last one needlessly.
some might say.

108
00:10:25.910 --> 00:10:29.209
Ser Arryk was awarded the great
duty of ending Rhaenyra's challenge.

109
00:10:29.210 --> 00:10:30.879
He failed to discharge it.

110
00:10:30.880 --> 00:10:32.379
He failed because
the scheme was rash.

111
00:10:32.380 --> 00:10:34.800
Perhaps. Your Grace. but
we cannot all hide in our castles

112
00:10:34.920 --> 00:10:36.010
waiting for war to come to us.

113
00:10:36.090 --> 00:10:37.470
As now it surely will.

114
00:10:37.590 --> 00:10:39.930
As. now. it already has.

115
00:10:40.720 --> 00:10:43.930
House Bracken took it upon
themselves to attack the Blackwoods.

116
00:10:44.060 --> 00:10:46.140
who declared for the pretender.

117
00:10:46.270 --> 00:10:48.229
Lord Samwell
Blackwood himself is slain.

118
00:10:48.230 --> 00:10:51.060
Good. First blood in our name.

119
00:10:51.440 --> 00:10:54.109
Both sides took heavy
losses. Your Grace.

120
00:10:54.110 --> 00:10:56.069
I-I'm not entirely certain

121
00:10:56.070 --> 00:10:57.899
we can declare this a victory.

122
00:10:57.900 --> 00:10:59.069
(sighs) The Blackwoods
and the Brackens

123
00:10:59.070 --> 00:11:00.160
have feuded for centuries.

124
00:11:00.280 --> 00:11:01.409
This is nothing more

125
00:11:01.410 --> 00:11:02.820
than an excuse
for them to indulge

126
00:11:02.950 --> 00:11:04.990
their ancient grudge.
It's no true war.

127
00:11:06.330 --> 00:11:10.460
Call it what you
will... I call it war.

128
00:11:11.290 --> 00:11:12.630
And so will Dragonstone.

129
00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:17.460
The question is. what are
we going to do about it?

130
00:11:22.970 --> 00:11:25.640
We send a raven to Lord Tully.

131
00:11:25.760 --> 00:11:27.850
These houses are his
vassals. are they not?

132
00:11:27.970 --> 00:11:31.939
- He must control them.
- Lord Grover Tully is a flaccid. old fool

133
00:11:31.940 --> 00:11:34.269
who couldn't control
his cock in a cunny.

134
00:11:34.270 --> 00:11:35.860
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

135
00:11:35.980 --> 00:11:38.200
Do you have
any better suggestions. Lord Jasper?

136
00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:40.109
Your lord uncle Ormund
marches from Oldtown

137
00:11:40.110 --> 00:11:42.320
at the head of a great
host. Your Grace.

138
00:11:42.450 --> 00:11:44.989
And your brother Daeron's
dragon nears fighting age.

139
00:11:44.990 --> 00:11:46.279
Call on them to
suppress the Riverlands.

140
00:11:46.280 --> 00:11:47.949
Alas. they are months away.

141
00:11:47.950 --> 00:11:49.160
My lord brother Jason

142
00:11:49.290 --> 00:11:51.289
is raising a great
army at Casterly Rock.

143
00:11:51.290 --> 00:11:53.040
In a matter of
weeks. he will be able

144
00:11:53.170 --> 00:11:54.789
to harass the
Blackwoods from the west.

145
00:11:54.790 --> 00:11:56.839
Should
we not aim to unite these armies

146
00:11:56.840 --> 00:11:58.340
and then strike as one?

147
00:11:58.460 --> 00:12:01.129
The great military
mind of the Citadel.

148
00:12:01.130 --> 00:12:02.969
- I served the realm...
- Do remind me.

149
00:12:02.970 --> 00:12:04.639
which link in your chain
denotes the art of war?

150
00:12:04.640 --> 00:12:06.969
This council must rediscover
the discipline it lately had

151
00:12:06.970 --> 00:12:08.350
if it's to be of any use.

152
00:12:08.470 --> 00:12:10.520
The Riverlands are
the key to the war.

153
00:12:11.180 --> 00:12:13.979
Harrenhal is the
key to the Riverlands.

154
00:12:13.980 --> 00:12:15.730
I will ride out with
those I can muster here.

155
00:12:15.810 --> 00:12:17.520
Men I know. men I've trained.

156
00:12:17.650 --> 00:12:20.689
You need time to raise the
numbers to challenge the Rivermen.

157
00:12:20.690 --> 00:12:22.029
Speed is my ally.

158
00:12:22.030 --> 00:12:23.410
I will turn the Crownland houses

159
00:12:23.530 --> 00:12:25.199
who declared for
Rhaenyra to our cause.

160
00:12:25.200 --> 00:12:28.370
We will add their numbers
to our own and then turn west.

161
00:12:28.490 --> 00:12:30.200
Where I will enlist
the Brackens.

162
00:12:30.330 --> 00:12:33.920
subdue the Riverlands.
and take Harrenhal.

163
00:12:34.540 --> 00:12:36.920
So
Impatient to ride with so few men.

164
00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:40.209
So like to be destroyed by
the first stronghold you meet.

165
00:12:40.210 --> 00:12:42.590
- A bold scheme indeed.
- Well. the gods favor the bold.

166
00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:46.339
They did not favor Ser Arryk.

167
00:12:46.340 --> 00:12:48.510
What say you. my king?

168
00:12:50.220 --> 00:12:52.559
And you'll take
Aemond and Vhagar?

169
00:12:52.560 --> 00:12:55.520
Vhagar will remain here...

170
00:12:56.270 --> 00:12:57.560
to defend the city.

171
00:12:58.730 --> 00:13:01.399
Good. To war. then.

172
00:13:02.740 --> 00:13:04.359
- I'll come. too. with Sunfyre.
- Aegon.

173
00:13:04.360 --> 00:13:06.160
- Your Grace.
- You'll need a dragon.

174
00:13:06.240 --> 00:13:07.620
My plan is
not to draw attention.

175
00:13:07.700 --> 00:13:10.790
And-And what will you do if
you encounter one or more

176
00:13:10.910 --> 00:13:12.039
of Rhaenyra's dragons?

177
00:13:12.040 --> 00:13:13.369
She'll want to
answer for Ser Arryk.

178
00:13:13.370 --> 00:13:15.079
We will be more
like to encounter one

179
00:13:15.080 --> 00:13:16.250
if we field one of our own.

180
00:13:16.460 --> 00:13:19.290
That is precisely why
you must remain. brother.

181
00:13:19.420 --> 00:13:23.260
It's a brave thought. but
we cannot risk your loss.

182
00:13:27.260 --> 00:13:30.140
I'm as fearsome as any of them.

183
00:13:55.830 --> 00:13:59.079
I was told you turned
back from your ship to bring warning.

184
00:13:59.080 --> 00:14:01.959
I was not believed at first.

185
00:14:01.960 --> 00:14:03.510
You saved my life.

186
00:14:03.800 --> 00:14:07.089
What is the life of a
queen worth these days?

187
00:14:07.090 --> 00:14:09.639
You wish to be rewarded.

188
00:14:09.640 --> 00:14:12.350
As. I would think. you
would wish to reward me.

189
00:14:15.480 --> 00:14:17.190
What price would you set?

190
00:14:17.310 --> 00:14:19.770
A place at your court.

191
00:14:23.530 --> 00:14:26.030
You said your earnest
desire was to flee Westeros.

192
00:14:26.150 --> 00:14:27.700
And you let me go.

193
00:14:27.820 --> 00:14:31.830
You showed me grace when
you could have withheld it.

194
00:14:32.990 --> 00:14:35.160
I'm not often surprised.

195
00:14:38.870 --> 00:14:41.130
One turn for another. then.

196
00:14:41.540 --> 00:14:43.799
I know the workings
of the Red Keep.

197
00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:47.129
and the movements of
those who serve there.

198
00:14:47.130 --> 00:14:50.050
That is worth more
than gold to you now.

199
00:14:50.510 --> 00:14:52.470
And what is my worth to you?

200
00:14:56.310 --> 00:14:57.979
I would punish the Hightowers

201
00:14:57.980 --> 00:14:59.520
for what they have done.

202
00:14:59.640 --> 00:15:03.060
To me... to those who served me.

203
00:15:03.860 --> 00:15:06.319
But more than that.
I know the struggles

204
00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:08.530
of the smallfolk
of King's Landing.

205
00:15:08.650 --> 00:15:12.820
They will be ruled either
by you or by the usurper.

206
00:15:13.530 --> 00:15:16.700
And only one of you has
shown yourself to be merciful.

207
00:15:17.540 --> 00:15:20.920
Well. I hope you do not
confuse mercy with pliancy.

208
00:15:24.210 --> 00:15:26.170
Are they always like this?

209
00:15:26.880 --> 00:15:29.760
Seasmoke. my late
lord husband's dragon.

210
00:15:30.880 --> 00:15:32.679
He's grown restless of late.

211
00:15:32.680 --> 00:15:36.010
- We cannot know why.
- Maybe he's lonely.

212
00:15:44.900 --> 00:15:46.610
Rhaena.

213
00:15:47.730 --> 00:15:49.280
Your Grace.

214
00:15:51.530 --> 00:15:54.029
I've decided to
send Joffrey to ward

215
00:15:54.030 --> 00:15:56.699
with my cousin.
Lady Jeyne Arryn.

216
00:15:56.700 --> 00:15:59.290
She has pledged an
army in return for a dragon.

217
00:15:59.410 --> 00:16:00.370
so she will have one.

218
00:16:00.371 --> 00:16:02.420
Aegon and Viserys
will accompany him

219
00:16:02.540 --> 00:16:04.879
until a place of greater
safety can be found.

220
00:16:04.880 --> 00:16:06.460
Tyraxes is but a hatchling.

221
00:16:06.880 --> 00:16:09.590
- And Stormcloud... - I
want you to go with them.

222
00:16:11.630 --> 00:16:13.640
The Red Keep is in disarray.

223
00:16:13.760 --> 00:16:15.259
They have sent one
assassin in the night

224
00:16:15.260 --> 00:16:17.430
and their dragons are
ever a short flight away.

225
00:16:17.890 --> 00:16:21.229
You must take the little ones
further. To Pentos. I think.

226
00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:22.389
Where my mother died.

227
00:16:22.390 --> 00:16:25.270
It is safer than
anywhere in Westeros.

228
00:16:26.150 --> 00:16:27.229
Write to Prince Reggio.

229
00:16:27.230 --> 00:16:30.110
If he will have
you. then go to him.

230
00:16:30.610 --> 00:16:32.609
I am sorry to put this upon you.

231
00:16:32.610 --> 00:16:35.279
It breaks my heart to
send my boys away.

232
00:16:35.280 --> 00:16:36.700
not knowing when I
will see them again.

233
00:16:36.780 --> 00:16:40.120
But you have seen what
may befall them here.

234
00:16:40.250 --> 00:16:41.620
Rhaena...

235
00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:46.500
I need you to be the
mother to them that I cannot.

236
00:16:47.630 --> 00:16:49.299
Teach them. train them.

237
00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:51.670
guard them as a
dragon guards her eggs.

238
00:16:51.800 --> 00:16:52.970
And my sister?

239
00:16:54.590 --> 00:16:56.510
- I need Baela here.
- Because she has a dragon.

240
00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:58.350
I cannot promise
to make you happy.

241
00:16:58.470 --> 00:17:00.599
But I ask you:

242
00:17:00.600 --> 00:17:03.139
make this sacrifice willingly.

243
00:17:03.140 --> 00:17:04.480
for all of us.

244
00:17:06.270 --> 00:17:07.650
Your Grace.

245
00:17:45.230 --> 00:17:47.060
Dragon!

246
00:20:21.010 --> 00:20:22.180
Halt!

247
00:20:36.190 --> 00:20:37.980
I'm claiming Harrenhal.

248
00:20:40.530 --> 00:20:42.240
Apparently so.

249
00:21:03.550 --> 00:21:06.720
I. Ser Simon Strong.
Castellan of Harrenhal.

250
00:21:06.850 --> 00:21:09.679
pledge fealty to Rhaenyra
of House Targaryen.

251
00:21:09.680 --> 00:21:11.600
First of Her Name.

252
00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:14.560
I swear this by the
old gods and the new.

253
00:21:16.060 --> 00:21:19.900
Supper is venison with
black cabbage and peas.

254
00:21:20.030 --> 00:21:23.900
No redcurrant. Sorry about that.

255
00:21:32.080 --> 00:21:34.580
That venison is well aged.

256
00:21:35.580 --> 00:21:37.210
Shame to let it waste.

257
00:21:40.920 --> 00:21:42.209
I've survived many a battle.

258
00:21:42.210 --> 00:21:44.970
I do not mean to be
felled by poisoned peas.

259
00:21:45.090 --> 00:21:47.889
(chuckles) I'll admit
that my cook's peas

260
00:21:47.890 --> 00:21:51.219
aren't exactly the stuff
of legend. but poison?

261
00:21:51.220 --> 00:21:54.730
Well. it's
an easy way to kill a dragonrider.

262
00:21:56.060 --> 00:21:59.440
If you've not yet surmised.
you are welcome here.

263
00:21:59.770 --> 00:22:04.110
And what of your
lord. Larys Strong?

264
00:22:04.780 --> 00:22:06.909
He who sits at the
false court of Aegon?

265
00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:10.330
Larys Clubfoot
is no lord of mine.

266
00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:14.950
He is a scourge upon
this castle and this family.

267
00:22:15.790 --> 00:22:19.000
Do you not think it's
strange that his father...

268
00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:24.759
my nephew. Lord
Lyonel. perished by fire?

269
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:29.300
And his son. too. here
in this damp place?

270
00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:32.810
It was the first fire here
since Balerion ended

271
00:22:32.930 --> 00:22:34.310
the line of Harren the Black.

272
00:22:34.970 --> 00:22:37.020
Even in the summer. we
struggle to light the hearths.

273
00:22:37.100 --> 00:22:40.609
So. no. you will find no loyalty
to Larys Strong here. my prince.

274
00:22:40.610 --> 00:22:41.980
"Your Grace."

275
00:22:47.320 --> 00:22:49.160
Forgive me. I-I. um...

276
00:22:50.820 --> 00:22:53.829
I... I'd only assumed
that as consort...

277
00:22:53.830 --> 00:22:56.660
Then we are reminded of the
perilousness of assumption.

278
00:22:58.160 --> 00:22:59.330
Indeed.

279
00:23:02.290 --> 00:23:03.840
Your Grace.

280
00:23:08.470 --> 00:23:11.850
What then brings you to
our corner of the Riverlands?

281
00:23:11.970 --> 00:23:15.180
Harrenhal is the largest
castle in the Seven Kingdoms.

282
00:23:16.020 --> 00:23:17.979
Or perhaps that has
escaped your attention.

283
00:23:17.980 --> 00:23:19.979
But it is also. not
to be argumentative.

284
00:23:19.980 --> 00:23:21.979
in something of
a state of disrepair

285
00:23:21.980 --> 00:23:25.360
since your forbear incinerated
much of it with his dragon.

286
00:23:25.480 --> 00:23:29.819
Well. that is precisely why we
must bring it into a state of repair.

287
00:23:29.820 --> 00:23:33.160
Even if we possessed
the coin. my prin...

288
00:23:34.330 --> 00:23:36.659
Your Grace. to
what possible end?

289
00:23:36.660 --> 00:23:38.750
There are 40.000
swords in the Riverlands.

290
00:23:38.870 --> 00:23:40.710
the largest undeclared
host in the realm.

291
00:23:40.830 --> 00:23:43.499
Only Harrenhal is of a size
enough to garrison them.

292
00:23:43.500 --> 00:23:44.879
You should know that
a substantial number

293
00:23:44.880 --> 00:23:46.710
of those swords
have now declared

294
00:23:46.840 --> 00:23:48.379
and are presently at war.

295
00:23:48.380 --> 00:23:51.839
Houses Bracken and Blackwood
have long detested one another.

296
00:23:51.840 --> 00:23:54.220
- Why?
- Well...

297
00:23:55.760 --> 00:24:00.350
the answer to that
is... lost in time.

298
00:24:01.390 --> 00:24:05.070
Sin begets sin begets sin.

299
00:24:07.730 --> 00:24:08.899
Summon your lord paramount

300
00:24:08.900 --> 00:24:10.570
so that I may treat
with him myself

301
00:24:10.700 --> 00:24:12.110
and turn them to our cause.

302
00:24:12.240 --> 00:24:15.699
That would be Lord Grover
Tully. but he grows frail.

303
00:24:15.700 --> 00:24:18.120
It's said that he can
no longer speak...

304
00:24:19.410 --> 00:24:21.410
nor seal his bowels.

305
00:24:21.750 --> 00:24:23.539
Begging your pardon
for the impression.

306
00:24:23.540 --> 00:24:25.039
His grip on his
bannermen is weak.

307
00:24:25.040 --> 00:24:26.480
They feel they can
do as they please.

308
00:24:26.590 --> 00:24:28.089
I will speak with
him nonetheless.

309
00:24:28.090 --> 00:24:30.550
People should
obey their liege lord...

310
00:24:31.470 --> 00:24:34.049
whatever his condition.

311
00:24:34.050 --> 00:24:36.300
Perhaps the
presence of the crown

312
00:24:37.430 --> 00:24:38.930
and a dragon

313
00:24:39.390 --> 00:24:42.270
will sharpen minds
around these parts.

314
00:24:43.600 --> 00:24:45.940
Might I ask. Your Grace...

315
00:24:46.770 --> 00:24:47.899
if you are successful.

316
00:24:47.900 --> 00:24:50.439
w-well. when you
are successful...

317
00:24:50.440 --> 00:24:52.820
what then?

318
00:24:52.950 --> 00:24:55.780
We march on King's
Landing and take the throne.

319
00:24:57.660 --> 00:24:59.290
The throne.

320
00:25:02.500 --> 00:25:06.420
It's a big chair made of swords.

321
00:25:07.290 --> 00:25:10.919
Standard-bearers to the front!

322
00:25:10.920 --> 00:25:13.510
Packhorses to the rear!

323
00:25:14.010 --> 00:25:16.680
Clear way for the
mounted knights...

324
00:25:27.650 --> 00:25:31.650
Lord Commander. Your host
is mustered and ready to march.

325
00:25:31.780 --> 00:25:33.949
He enjoys battle.

326
00:25:38.320 --> 00:25:40.489
I'm glad we're
together. even briefly.

327
00:25:40.490 --> 00:25:43.119
Ser Criston.

328
00:25:43.120 --> 00:25:46.040
May I present my brother.
Ser Gwayne Hightower.

329
00:25:46.170 --> 00:25:48.289
arrived last night from Oldtown.

330
00:25:48.290 --> 00:25:49.500
Ser Criston.

331
00:25:50.340 --> 00:25:54.300
Or mayhaps I should
say. my lord Hand?

332
00:25:54.670 --> 00:25:56.680
Ser Gwayne. welcome
to King's Landing.

333
00:25:57.220 --> 00:26:00.560
How exhilarating to
arrive at court after

334
00:26:00.680 --> 00:26:02.349
three long months on the road

335
00:26:02.350 --> 00:26:04.639
to find my lord father.

336
00:26:04.640 --> 00:26:06.849
who served three
kings faithfully.

337
00:26:06.850 --> 00:26:08.520
unseated as Hand of the King.

338
00:26:10.520 --> 00:26:14.189
And by a man from
such modest beginnings.

339
00:26:15.530 --> 00:26:20.159
What a giddying ascent the
gods have bestowed on you.

340
00:26:20.160 --> 00:26:23.330
Ser Gwayne has volunteered
to accompany you into battle.

341
00:26:27.210 --> 00:26:29.169
We have a full
complement. Your Grace.

342
00:26:29.170 --> 00:26:31.420
Then you shall
have a fuller one.

343
00:26:33.090 --> 00:26:34.840
The march will be hard. Ser.

344
00:26:35.340 --> 00:26:37.339
No one is more delighted than I

345
00:26:37.340 --> 00:26:39.430
to march out to war
with a Dornishman.

346
00:26:41.220 --> 00:26:42.220
Sister.

347
00:26:50.060 --> 00:26:53.359
May the Seven guide
you. good knight...

348
00:26:53.360 --> 00:26:56.070
and lead you not into
shadow and death.

349
00:26:57.900 --> 00:26:59.740
I thank Your Grace
for her prayers.

350
00:27:03.410 --> 00:27:05.910
And request that
she grant her favor...

351
00:27:07.040 --> 00:27:10.080
that her Lord Commander may
go into battle with her blessings

352
00:27:11.540 --> 00:27:13.250
in his heart.

353
00:27:24.930 --> 00:27:26.270
Your Grace.

354
00:27:37.820 --> 00:27:39.450
Hyah!

355
00:28:16.320 --> 00:28:19.150
Still no sightings.

356
00:28:19.280 --> 00:28:24.160
No men. no horses. no ships.

357
00:28:25.990 --> 00:28:27.789
- No dragons.
- Good.

358
00:28:27.790 --> 00:28:32.459
Then we must seize the hour
and act before our enemy does.

359
00:28:32.460 --> 00:28:33.959
They have penetrated
our castle walls.

360
00:28:33.960 --> 00:28:35.340
and now the
Riverlands are aflame

361
00:28:35.460 --> 00:28:37.670
after the Battle
at the Burning Mill.

362
00:28:38.130 --> 00:28:40.840
How fares Prince
Daemon with our army?

363
00:28:41.800 --> 00:28:45.139
There has been no word from
Prince Daemon. Your Grace.

364
00:28:45.140 --> 00:28:47.720
Then we must press what
advantage we do have.

365
00:28:47.850 --> 00:28:51.180
- And what is that?
- Dragons. Send them all out.

366
00:28:51.310 --> 00:28:55.149
Start turning Green
strongholds to our cause

367
00:28:55.150 --> 00:28:57.690
- and burn those who resist.
- No.

368
00:28:58.320 --> 00:29:00.189
If dragons begin
fighting dragons.

369
00:29:00.190 --> 00:29:02.989
we invite our own destruction.

370
00:29:02.990 --> 00:29:05.200
Fear of it is in
itself a weapon.

371
00:29:05.820 --> 00:29:09.200
The Greens will make the same calculation.

372
00:29:10.540 --> 00:29:14.370
The value of a sword is
not within its scabbard.

373
00:29:14.870 --> 00:29:17.539
We will secure
victory with armies.

374
00:29:17.540 --> 00:29:19.590
not with dragons alone.

375
00:29:20.880 --> 00:29:22.220
The Greens understand that.

376
00:29:22.590 --> 00:29:25.220
The Vale and the
North will send men.

377
00:29:26.340 --> 00:29:28.560
We must give Daemon time.

378
00:29:29.010 --> 00:29:32.770
Your Grace. you have
witnessed firsthand just how

379
00:29:32.890 --> 00:29:34.390
vulnerable you are.

380
00:29:34.520 --> 00:29:36.519
Prince Daemon is abroad.

381
00:29:36.520 --> 00:29:39.729
and Aegon's factions are
enraged at the death of his son.

382
00:29:39.730 --> 00:29:41.689
You have never been so exposed.

383
00:29:41.690 --> 00:29:43.900
Perhaps it is time
for you to think about

384
00:29:44.030 --> 00:29:46.569
secreting yourself
somewhere safe.

385
00:29:46.570 --> 00:29:47.699
while we remain here

386
00:29:47.700 --> 00:29:51.699
as a source of
distraction for the enemy.

387
00:29:51.700 --> 00:29:53.620
You propose to conduct
the war in my absence.

388
00:29:53.750 --> 00:29:57.420
- It would merely be a
precaution... - It would be treason.

389
00:30:00.460 --> 00:30:02.920
You are fortunate
you took it no further.

390
00:30:10.600 --> 00:30:12.270
This council would
do well to remember

391
00:30:12.390 --> 00:30:14.980
that their queen wears
the crown of my grandsire.

392
00:30:15.100 --> 00:30:17.310
Jaehaerys the Conciliator.

393
00:30:17.770 --> 00:30:21.069
A prudent ruler. the
wisest of Targaryen kings.

394
00:30:21.070 --> 00:30:23.610
whose reign
outlasted every other...

395
00:30:25.820 --> 00:30:28.240
even Aegon the Conqueror's.

396
00:30:33.620 --> 00:30:35.579
<i>So. how do they fare?</i>

397
00:30:35.580 --> 00:30:37.619
<i>The ditherers of Dragonstone?</i>

398
00:30:37.620 --> 00:30:41.840
Rhaenyra's council
is wayward. She has a hard task.

399
00:30:41.960 --> 00:30:43.959
I must hope she will rise to it.

400
00:30:43.960 --> 00:30:47.470
but I fear she'll need you
by her side sooner than late.

401
00:30:47.590 --> 00:30:49.800
This bread. still warm.

402
00:30:50.430 --> 00:30:52.640
There's broth too.
I made sure of it.

403
00:30:53.970 --> 00:30:56.140
I am no longer an invalid.

404
00:31:02.650 --> 00:31:05.860
I bade farewell to
Rhaena before I returned.

405
00:31:09.280 --> 00:31:10.990
I wish her well.

406
00:31:12.660 --> 00:31:15.119
I would fight a hundred
battles before I went into exile

407
00:31:15.120 --> 00:31:17.460
with none but prattling babes.

408
00:31:18.540 --> 00:31:20.999
One of those babes is your heir.

409
00:31:21.000 --> 00:31:22.960
(scoffs) Joffrey.

410
00:31:23.500 --> 00:31:26.969
A boy of six who
knows nothing of the sea

411
00:31:26.970 --> 00:31:28.510
and yet somehow...

412
00:31:29.010 --> 00:31:32.179
It would displease neither
Rhaenyra nor the gods

413
00:31:32.180 --> 00:31:36.180
if Rhaena were
named heir to Driftmark.

414
00:31:38.230 --> 00:31:41.230
Rhaena? Lord of the Tides?

415
00:31:41.730 --> 00:31:44.570
The girl knows nothing of
ships. nor even of dragons.

416
00:31:44.690 --> 00:31:47.190
There is Rhaena
or there is Joffrey.

417
00:31:47.740 --> 00:31:51.990
Both soon to be far from the
creak of ships and the ocean's roar.

418
00:31:53.370 --> 00:31:57.540
Then we must hope to...

419
00:31:58.040 --> 00:32:00.329
see our way forward. in time.

420
00:32:00.330 --> 00:32:02.710
And if there is no time?

421
00:32:05.210 --> 00:32:07.550
We are at war. Corlys.

422
00:32:09.050 --> 00:32:14.100
- If something were to
befall you... - Then... it is well

423
00:32:14.220 --> 00:32:16.220
that I am a good sailor.

424
00:32:29.740 --> 00:32:31.739
I have much to attend to.

425
00:32:31.740 --> 00:32:33.240
Corlys. Corl...

426
00:32:56.760 --> 00:32:59.059
I cannot spare
a fighting dragon.

427
00:32:59.060 --> 00:33:00.389
but I send what I can.

428
00:33:00.390 --> 00:33:02.769
Stormcloud and
Tyraxes are small.

429
00:33:02.770 --> 00:33:05.439
but they will grow.

430
00:33:05.440 --> 00:33:08.399
It is for you to remind
Lady Jeyne of her pledge

431
00:33:08.400 --> 00:33:12.320
and persuade her of
the urgency of our need.

432
00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.950
Go safely. sister.

433
00:33:22.290 --> 00:33:24.460
I will be safe enough.

434
00:33:24.580 --> 00:33:26.419
Far away from any danger.

435
00:33:26.420 --> 00:33:28.170
with only babes to nursemaid.

436
00:33:28.290 --> 00:33:30.419
You do a great service.

437
00:33:30.420 --> 00:33:32.259
and may yet find yourself
glad to be out of harm's way.

438
00:33:32.260 --> 00:33:34.470
Do not coddle me. Baela.

439
00:33:34.590 --> 00:33:37.180
- Grant me at least that dignity.
- I meant no insult.

440
00:33:37.300 --> 00:33:39.429
We each do what we can.

441
00:33:39.430 --> 00:33:42.520
And here. I think.
is some consolation.

442
00:33:44.850 --> 00:33:48.110
Tyraxes and Stormcloud
are young and vulnerable.

443
00:33:49.150 --> 00:33:52.490
These eggs are
even more fragile.

444
00:33:53.490 --> 00:33:56.660
But should all
come to ruin here...

445
00:33:57.660 --> 00:33:59.870
you will bear our
hope for the future.

446
00:34:02.370 --> 00:34:03.620
Your Grace.

447
00:34:04.330 --> 00:34:06.540
Mommy.

448
00:35:41.590 --> 00:35:43.140
My Queen.

449
00:35:45.430 --> 00:35:48.599
I feel sad about Jaehaerys.

450
00:35:48.600 --> 00:35:51.600
But I ought not to. I think.

451
00:35:52.310 --> 00:35:54.569
People die all the time.

452
00:35:54.570 --> 00:35:56.480
especially babes.

453
00:35:57.070 --> 00:36:01.110
They're so little. s-so
they're taken so easily.

454
00:36:04.450 --> 00:36:07.409
Sadness is a condition
of motherhood.

455
00:36:07.410 --> 00:36:09.790
There's naught to
be gained from it.

456
00:36:14.250 --> 00:36:17.799
That horrid procession where
the smallfolk all stared at me.

457
00:36:17.800 --> 00:36:22.090
I warrant they thought I had no
more right to grief than they do.

458
00:36:24.300 --> 00:36:28.020
Surely they lose their babes
more than highborn ladies.

459
00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:34.190
The Stranger comes for us all...

460
00:36:35.320 --> 00:36:37.030
queen and commoner.

461
00:36:38.860 --> 00:36:41.650
You have as much
claim to grief as anyone.

462
00:36:43.820 --> 00:36:44.990
And you?

463
00:36:49.500 --> 00:36:51.159
I loved Jaehaerys. but
my concern has been

464
00:36:51.160 --> 00:36:54.000
more for you and
what you have endured.

465
00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:59.510
- Helaena.
I... - I forgive you.

466
00:37:01.010 --> 00:37:02.180
What?

467
00:37:07.310 --> 00:37:09.310
I said that I forgive you.

468
00:37:14.810 --> 00:37:17.360
Suits you. Your Grace.

469
00:37:17.730 --> 00:37:20.900
Valyrian steel. Worth
more than a castle.

470
00:37:21.030 --> 00:37:23.360
A sight to stir the passions.

471
00:37:23.860 --> 00:37:26.030
Aegon the Conqueror reborn.

472
00:37:26.160 --> 00:37:27.369
Just get on with it.

473
00:37:27.370 --> 00:37:28.700
At once. Your Grace.

474
00:37:28.830 --> 00:37:30.369
What is your business?

475
00:37:30.370 --> 00:37:33.580
There are rumors that the
King readies himself to fly to war.

476
00:37:34.170 --> 00:37:36.170
And what is it to you?

477
00:37:36.670 --> 00:37:38.130
Only that I think it
would benefit all of us

478
00:37:38.210 --> 00:37:41.590
to prevent our king from being
brutally slain by our enemies.

479
00:37:41.720 --> 00:37:43.879
and his body parts
scattered to beasts.

480
00:37:43.880 --> 00:37:45.260
and his court come to ruin.

481
00:37:45.390 --> 00:37:46.890
Would you not agree?

482
00:37:49.680 --> 00:37:51.730
What exquisite armor.

483
00:37:54.390 --> 00:37:57.519
I was given the Conqueror's
name and his crown.

484
00:37:57.520 --> 00:37:59.730
so I shall wear
his armor to war.

485
00:37:59.860 --> 00:38:03.110
I fly to meet Ser Criston.

486
00:38:03.240 --> 00:38:06.240
Small imposition before
you depart then. Your Grace.

487
00:38:17.080 --> 00:38:20.749
There are diverse rumors
whispered on the streets of your city.

488
00:38:20.750 --> 00:38:24.049
One such is that Your Grace
sends his forces to battle.

489
00:38:24.050 --> 00:38:25.590
and. in his courage and wisdom.

490
00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:27.430
flies with them.

491
00:38:29.470 --> 00:38:33.099
Another is that His Grace
was outwitted by his counselors

492
00:38:33.100 --> 00:38:36.270
and persuaded to fly
to war with Ser Criston.

493
00:38:36.390 --> 00:38:38.310
so that Queen Alicent

494
00:38:38.440 --> 00:38:40.770
may reign in his absence

495
00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:43.990
with Prince Aemond at her side.

496
00:38:45.450 --> 00:38:47.110
Absurd. of course.

497
00:38:48.780 --> 00:38:51.950
(inhales) Who
spreads these lies?

498
00:38:52.620 --> 00:38:54.330
It matters little.

499
00:38:54.790 --> 00:38:57.120
Tales take on a
life of their own...

500
00:38:58.000 --> 00:38:59.170
like weeds.

501
00:38:59.630 --> 00:39:01.800
Unless they are tended.

502
00:39:02.750 --> 00:39:04.760
Well. tend to them then.

503
00:39:13.140 --> 00:39:14.310
Lord Larys.

504
00:39:16.180 --> 00:39:18.690
My father always
said he had no use

505
00:39:18.810 --> 00:39:20.860
for a master of whisperers.

506
00:39:22.110 --> 00:39:26.490
And yet... I find
myself wanting for one.

507
00:39:27.990 --> 00:39:30.780
I should be glad
of your talents.

508
00:39:34.700 --> 00:39:36.960
You honor me. Your Grace.

509
00:39:43.040 --> 00:39:46.300
Shall we escort
you to the Dragonpit. Your Grace?

510
00:39:52.890 --> 00:39:55.139
I think. mayhaps. I
shall fly another day.

511
00:39:55.140 --> 00:39:58.730
- (group agrees) - Yeah. it-it
does seem wise on reflection.

512
00:39:58.850 --> 00:40:00.979
You could come
out with us. my king.

513
00:40:00.980 --> 00:40:03.520
Ser Martyn has a new
squire that wants bedding in.

514
00:40:03.860 --> 00:40:06.400
He's never fucked a woman.

515
00:40:06.860 --> 00:40:09.860
But you are sworn to chastity now.

516
00:40:11.820 --> 00:40:14.370
Of course. Your Grace. (laughs)

517
00:40:19.750 --> 00:40:21.500
Yes. Your Grace.

518
00:40:58.240 --> 00:41:00.369
No. no. no. no. no. no.
Don't tell me you're going.

519
00:41:00.370 --> 00:41:02.790
- I'm not going yet.
- I've only just got here.

520
00:41:06.750 --> 00:41:07.800
There he is!

521
00:41:09.710 --> 00:41:12.430
Ulf. Ulf. come on. son!

522
00:41:14.090 --> 00:41:16.259
It turns out. it was her sister.

523
00:41:16.260 --> 00:41:18.260
- (laughter) - Probably
should've told me.

524
00:41:18.390 --> 00:41:21.229
I know. I know. I know!

525
00:41:21.230 --> 00:41:23.520
Take that one. You'll get
your pound of flesh. don't worry.

526
00:41:23.600 --> 00:41:25.110
Sit yourself down. mate.

527
00:41:25.230 --> 00:41:27.399
- Hello.
- I've been tellin' this fella all about you.

528
00:41:27.400 --> 00:41:29.110
Lads.

529
00:41:29.230 --> 00:41:31.440
- I've had quite a day of it.
- Yeah?

530
00:41:31.570 --> 00:41:33.450
Not sure I'm much for talkin'.

531
00:41:34.280 --> 00:41:37.950
Although. you know. a
wet whistle works wonders.

532
00:41:42.500 --> 00:41:45.419
Come on. Ulf. give us a
flagon over there. yeah?

533
00:41:45.420 --> 00:41:48.749
Yeah. my darling. one for
the flagon. one for yourself.

534
00:41:48.750 --> 00:41:50.919
There's a good girl?

535
00:41:54.970 --> 00:41:56.759
No sense of fun. some of 'em.

536
00:41:56.760 --> 00:42:00.430
- For you. man of Dorne.
- Dornish. are ya?

537
00:42:01.310 --> 00:42:05.099
- Yes. I am.
- The part of Westeros my house never settled.

538
00:42:05.100 --> 00:42:06.439
Although. it's said even Dorne

539
00:42:06.440 --> 00:42:09.320
mourned the passing of
my grandsire. Is that so?

540
00:42:09.770 --> 00:42:11.480
Who was your grandsire?

541
00:42:14.990 --> 00:42:18.490
They call him the Conciliator.

542
00:42:18.620 --> 00:42:20.990
- King Jaehaerys?
- Shh!

543
00:42:22.200 --> 00:42:25.499
Thousand apologies.
Please. continue.

544
00:42:25.500 --> 00:42:28.500
Look. I-I really shouldn't
be telling you this.

545
00:42:29.380 --> 00:42:30.550
You'll cost me my head.

546
00:42:30.670 --> 00:42:33.510
- You are saying you're a Targaryen?
- Shh-shh-shh.

547
00:42:38.300 --> 00:42:41.680
I'm the son of Baelon the Brave.

548
00:42:42.310 --> 00:42:45.390
Bastard brother to Prince Daemon

549
00:42:45.520 --> 00:42:47.189
and the late King Viserys.

550
00:42:47.190 --> 00:42:52.650
Uncle to the one true
queen. Rhaenyra Targaryen.

551
00:42:53.400 --> 00:42:56.199
The blood of the dragon
runs through these veins.

552
00:42:56.200 --> 00:42:59.990
And. yes... men would
take my head for it.

553
00:43:02.370 --> 00:43:04.539
A Dragonseed must
watch his own neck

554
00:43:04.540 --> 00:43:08.540
when he has no white-cloaked
guardsmen to do it for him.

555
00:43:10.210 --> 00:43:12.710
You do not look very
much like King Viserys

556
00:43:13.710 --> 00:43:15.340
or Prince Daemon.

557
00:43:17.380 --> 00:43:19.179
(sighs) How do you
know what they look like?

558
00:43:19.180 --> 00:43:21.179
He speaks truth. right enough.

559
00:43:21.180 --> 00:43:24.600
Look. you can
tell... by his hair.

560
00:43:24.720 --> 00:43:28.060
- (laughter) - Yeah. 'cause I'm
their half-brother. you fuckwit.

561
00:43:28.190 --> 00:43:30.519
Yeah. I'll tell you who else
doesn't have silver hair.

562
00:43:30.520 --> 00:43:32.270
The rightful heir
to the Iron Throne.

563
00:43:32.400 --> 00:43:35.359
my nephew. Prince
Jacaerys Velaryon.

564
00:43:39.240 --> 00:43:41.200
Here's your other nephew.

565
00:43:48.210 --> 00:43:53.039
- All hail the King!
- All hail the King!

566
00:43:53.040 --> 00:43:56.760
Drinks for all! At the
pleasure of the crown!

567
00:43:59.090 --> 00:44:03.930
- (laughter) - Woo! At
the pleasure of the crown!

568
00:44:05.060 --> 00:44:07.059
Sit down. Sit yourself down.

569
00:44:07.060 --> 00:44:09.229
- Sit!
- Drink the wine. boy.

570
00:44:09.230 --> 00:44:11.310
- Come on. then!
- Drink up. little piggy!

571
00:44:11.440 --> 00:44:14.820
This night is for you.

572
00:44:14.940 --> 00:44:16.940
You!

573
00:44:24.450 --> 00:44:27.949
(intoxicated) Did I. did I tell
you I came here as a lad?

574
00:44:27.950 --> 00:44:30.419
It's. a little tame.

575
00:44:30.420 --> 00:44:33.419
but a good a place
as any to get it wet.

576
00:44:33.420 --> 00:44:37.510
(laughs) I know just
the tutor for you. my boy.

577
00:44:40.760 --> 00:44:41.799
No.

578
00:44:41.800 --> 00:44:43.759
She's worth three
times the price.

579
00:44:46.430 --> 00:44:50.099
- Gods be good.
- (laughs) - That's you!

580
00:44:50.100 --> 00:44:52.439
Her name is. Sylvi

581
00:44:52.440 --> 00:44:56.520
or Selyse or. I don't
know. something like that.

582
00:45:05.660 --> 00:45:07.119
Aemond. the fierce!

583
00:45:07.120 --> 00:45:10.330
(laughing) You have come so far.

584
00:45:10.460 --> 00:45:13.789
and. and yet you still
lie with your very first.

585
00:45:15.000 --> 00:45:17.959
What a fine. sweet thing.

586
00:45:19.460 --> 00:45:21.720
Did you fuck her like a hound?

587
00:45:25.850 --> 00:45:27.969
You see. I do not exaggerate.

588
00:45:27.970 --> 00:45:30.020
Such is the madam's prowess.

589
00:45:30.140 --> 00:45:33.809
that even now my brother
will not sample another.

590
00:45:36.360 --> 00:45:38.189
Hard luck for your
squire. though.

591
00:45:38.190 --> 00:45:40.190
As you can see. she... (laughs)

592
00:45:40.320 --> 00:45:42.740
she's now very much occupied.

593
00:45:51.330 --> 00:45:53.499
Your squire is welcome to her.

594
00:45:55.000 --> 00:45:56.879
One whore is as good as another.

595
00:47:14.120 --> 00:47:17.330
Ser Gwayne! Halt!

596
00:47:22.300 --> 00:47:25.800
Ser Gwayne. our company
is camped back yonder.

597
00:47:26.260 --> 00:47:28.429
On the cold. hard ground.

598
00:47:28.430 --> 00:47:30.640
Which is why we
make for the Bull.

599
00:47:30.760 --> 00:47:32.470
a tavern with an
excellent reputation

600
00:47:32.600 --> 00:47:34.269
on the Rosby Road.
not two miles away.

601
00:47:34.270 --> 00:47:36.349
- if memory serves.
- We march to make the first strike

602
00:47:36.350 --> 00:47:37.810
in the name of His Grace.

603
00:47:38.480 --> 00:47:42.690
I assure you. my nephew will
not begrudge me a night of comfort.

604
00:47:48.200 --> 00:47:50.449
If it soothes your brow. Cole.

605
00:47:50.450 --> 00:47:53.620
we will rendezvous with
your army at first light.

606
00:47:53.990 --> 00:47:55.040
Or. if their wine is good.

607
00:47:55.160 --> 00:47:57.330
perhaps a little
after first light.

608
00:47:59.830 --> 00:48:01.840
- We're exposed.
- What?

609
00:48:03.550 --> 00:48:07.299
- Cole?
- Get to the trees!

610
00:48:07.300 --> 00:48:09.840
Hyah! Hyah!

611
00:48:38.000 --> 00:48:40.330
Hah! Hyah!

612
00:50:05.000 --> 00:50:07.000
A good showing. Ser Criston.

613
00:50:10.010 --> 00:50:13.970
- I am in your debt.
- They know we're abroad. They'll be hunting.

614
00:50:14.090 --> 00:50:15.220
And we must move under the trees

615
00:50:15.300 --> 00:50:17.640
and by cover of
dark. starting tonight.

616
00:50:18.470 --> 00:50:20.850
And no fucking inns.

617
00:50:23.810 --> 00:50:26.020
<i>Ser Criston Cole...</i>

618
00:50:26.480 --> 00:50:29.320
with some half-dozen
other knights. I'm sure of it.

619
00:50:29.440 --> 00:50:31.439
Perhaps a scout party
for a greater army.

620
00:50:31.440 --> 00:50:33.530
The
ravens confirm it. Your Grace.

621
00:50:33.650 --> 00:50:36.449
Lord Farring has
reported a larger force

622
00:50:36.450 --> 00:50:39.830
moving northeast towards Rosby.

623
00:50:39.950 --> 00:50:42.659
Could you be certain it was
Cole from such a great height?

624
00:50:42.660 --> 00:50:45.500
It was not such a great
height. Your Grace.

625
00:50:47.540 --> 00:50:50.840
You said not to engage.
so I didn't. exactly.

626
00:50:50.960 --> 00:50:55.179
Your Grace. we commend the
Lady Baela for her sharp eyes.

627
00:50:55.180 --> 00:50:56.629
but we can tarry no longer.

628
00:50:56.630 --> 00:50:59.009
The time for
action is surely now.

629
00:50:59.010 --> 00:51:00.469
Your Grace. I must agree

630
00:51:00.470 --> 00:51:01.679
and request your permission

631
00:51:01.680 --> 00:51:04.390
to return to Rook's
Rest and fortify my lands.

632
00:51:04.520 --> 00:51:06.110
- I
- shouldn't fret. Lord Simon.

633
00:51:06.190 --> 00:51:07.690
They'll be making for Harrenhal.

634
00:51:07.810 --> 00:51:09.649
'Tis Prince Daemon
who ought to worry.

635
00:51:09.650 --> 00:51:11.149
Prince Daemon has Caraxes.

636
00:51:11.150 --> 00:51:13.431
Cole will
look to increase his numbers.

637
00:51:13.530 --> 00:51:15.489
and he may call upon
a dragon of his own.

638
00:51:15.490 --> 00:51:19.319
This is why you must
act now. Your Grace.

639
00:51:19.320 --> 00:51:22.040
Loose the dragons. Root
Cole out and burn him.

640
00:51:38.090 --> 00:51:40.100
I have heard your arguments.

641
00:51:41.600 --> 00:51:44.179
And will consider them.

642
00:53:42.550 --> 00:53:45.970
Always coming and
going. aren't you?

643
00:53:51.690 --> 00:53:54.900
And I have to
clean up afterwards.

644
00:54:35.560 --> 00:54:37.690
You will die in this place.

645
00:54:56.420 --> 00:54:59.589
My youngest
brother. Emmon. would stand at guard

646
00:54:59.590 --> 00:55:01.589
with the soldiers when
he was three years old.

647
00:55:01.590 --> 00:55:02.919
Father has sent
him to the Citadel.

648
00:55:02.920 --> 00:55:05.760
- Now. if you ask me... -
Rhaenyra: Thank you. Elinda.

649
00:55:06.260 --> 00:55:07.430
Your Grace.

650
00:55:14.560 --> 00:55:17.940
What do you know of the
movements of Alicent Hightower?

651
00:55:21.110 --> 00:55:24.150
W-Would you take her hostage?

652
00:55:24.610 --> 00:55:26.610
Or kill her outright?

653
00:55:26.740 --> 00:55:30.490
I would speak with her. myself.

654
00:55:30.620 --> 00:55:33.080
Killing her would be easier.

655
00:55:34.160 --> 00:55:37.580
If war can be averted.
it is my duty to avert it.

656
00:55:38.120 --> 00:55:41.090
I have reason to believe she
may be of the same opinion.

657
00:55:41.800 --> 00:55:44.919
She sent a raven. She
has expressed her remorse.

658
00:55:44.920 --> 00:55:46.630
I can have a message
brought to her.

659
00:55:46.760 --> 00:55:49.429
- in secret.
- She would not agree to it.

660
00:55:49.430 --> 00:55:52.759
She would suspect
some subterfuge.

661
00:55:52.760 --> 00:55:55.309
as would I. if I received
such a message.

662
00:55:55.310 --> 00:55:58.810
I must see her face to face.

663
00:56:01.860 --> 00:56:03.779
She is the queen dowager.

664
00:56:03.780 --> 00:56:07.030
She goes nowhere without
many eyes watching her.

665
00:56:08.860 --> 00:56:12.120
(soft gasp) Unless...

666
00:56:16.000 --> 00:56:19.289
- 'Tis fraught.
- Speak it.

667
00:56:19.290 --> 00:56:23.839
There are fishing
boats aplenty in the bay.

668
00:56:23.840 --> 00:56:25.550
The city depends on them.

669
00:56:25.670 --> 00:56:27.969
Daemon made the
journey unhindered.

670
00:56:27.970 --> 00:56:31.139
- But if I'm recognized... - You
may be surprised to learn it.

671
00:56:31.140 --> 00:56:35.020
but most folk pay no mind to a
woman who has not dressed as a queen.

672
00:56:35.140 --> 00:56:38.350
or allured herself
for the eyes of men.

673
00:56:41.350 --> 00:56:44.730
So. I make my way to
the Red Keep. I presume.

674
00:56:44.860 --> 00:56:47.149
and ring the bell.

675
00:56:47.150 --> 00:56:49.859
Or do I scale the wall
and enter at her window?

676
00:56:49.860 --> 00:56:52.740
There is one place Alicent goes

677
00:56:52.870 --> 00:56:55.870
outside the castle walls...

678
00:56:56.660 --> 00:56:58.870
where you may
yet find her alone.

679
00:57:19.850 --> 00:57:22.059
Stop. Search the carts.

680
00:57:26.690 --> 00:57:28.229
What's your business here?

681
00:57:28.230 --> 00:57:31.910
Move 'em on
through. move 'em on through.

682
00:59:54.170 --> 00:59:56.420
(gasps) No. no. Shh.

683
00:59:56.550 --> 00:59:58.550
- What...
- Shh.

684
00:59:59.050 --> 01:00:02.010
- What... H... - I
must speak with you.

685
01:00:06.100 --> 01:00:08.729
If I c-cry out?

686
01:00:08.730 --> 01:00:09.770
Your knights would find me.

687
01:00:09.850 --> 01:00:11.900
I would be taken or slain.

688
01:00:12.020 --> 01:00:13.729
though not before I killed you.

689
01:00:13.730 --> 01:00:16.610
(exhales) And then what?

690
01:00:17.400 --> 01:00:18.530
W...

691
01:00:20.570 --> 01:00:24.040
(sighs) I have begun badly.

692
01:00:35.920 --> 01:00:38.759
We watched the tourney
together. you and I...

693
01:00:38.760 --> 01:00:41.550
the day my brother was born.

694
01:00:42.890 --> 01:00:45.810
We knew. even then. that
men trained up for battle

695
01:00:45.930 --> 01:00:49.940
are eager to fight. to
seek blood and glory.

696
01:00:50.270 --> 01:00:52.310
But you are... (sighs)

697
01:00:54.070 --> 01:00:57.440
I know you do not have
that desire within you.

698
01:01:03.450 --> 01:01:05.739
Rhaenys has counseled me.

699
01:01:05.740 --> 01:01:10.460
She said she saw in you a wish to
avert the worst of what may now come.

700
01:01:13.290 --> 01:01:16.759
So. you've come
to surrender then?

701
01:01:16.760 --> 01:01:21.680
I have come to see if we may
uncover some path towards peace.

702
01:01:22.970 --> 01:01:25.810
My dragons are
restless. They smell battle.

703
01:01:25.930 --> 01:01:28.099
But if you and I
may come to terms...

704
01:01:28.100 --> 01:01:30.480
There are no terms now.

705
01:01:31.810 --> 01:01:33.269
You have no army.

706
01:01:33.270 --> 01:01:35.319
your allies turn from you when
they hear of your depravity.

707
01:01:35.320 --> 01:01:37.149
your hands are bloodied in
a crime I could never have

708
01:01:37.150 --> 01:01:40.779
- imagined you... - The
trespass was not mine.

709
01:01:40.780 --> 01:01:42.320
Think what you will.

710
01:01:42.950 --> 01:01:45.489
I am a mother too and you have yet
to answer for the murder of my son.

711
01:01:45.490 --> 01:01:49.000
- I repudiate that act with all my heart.
- Of course. you do.

712
01:01:49.620 --> 01:01:53.170
And the usurping of
my rightful inheritance?

713
01:02:09.890 --> 01:02:11.180
Have you now stooped so low

714
01:02:11.310 --> 01:02:12.849
that you will
countenance the suffering

715
01:02:12.850 --> 01:02:14.350
and death of thousands.

716
01:02:14.480 --> 01:02:16.019
in order that your
feckless son...

717
01:02:16.020 --> 01:02:18.149
Your father changed his mind.

718
01:02:18.150 --> 01:02:19.530
So you say.

719
01:02:19.650 --> 01:02:22.360
And so your father has
proclaimed to the realm.

720
01:02:22.490 --> 01:02:25.370
I saw the king that night.

721
01:02:25.870 --> 01:02:27.159
Mere hours before I left him.

722
01:02:27.160 --> 01:02:29.329
he had affirmed my
right to the throne.

723
01:02:29.330 --> 01:02:32.250
a right he upheld steadfastly.

724
01:02:32.370 --> 01:02:35.210
every day of his life
after my mother died.

725
01:02:36.540 --> 01:02:38.709
And yet. you will maintain
that his mind was changed

726
01:02:38.710 --> 01:02:40.710
- in an instant?
- I will.

727
01:02:42.050 --> 01:02:44.679
You lie.

728
01:02:44.680 --> 01:02:46.390
(softly) No. Rhaenyra.

729
01:02:49.220 --> 01:02:51.390
My father loved me. Alicent.

730
01:02:51.890 --> 01:02:54.230
And I believe he loved you. too.

731
01:02:55.560 --> 01:02:57.770
Did you betray
him at the very last?

732
01:02:59.230 --> 01:03:01.359
When was your plan first laid?

733
01:03:01.360 --> 01:03:05.199
- Was your ambition so keen...
He changed his mind. Rhaenyra.

734
01:03:05.200 --> 01:03:07.120
He changed his mind.

735
01:03:11.240 --> 01:03:14.750
I swear this to you on
the memory of my mother.

736
01:03:18.590 --> 01:03:21.710
I have been. at times.
unkind. but never untrue.

737
01:03:22.090 --> 01:03:23.549
I pronounced before
all gathered in that room

738
01:03:23.550 --> 01:03:26.300
that you would
make a fine queen.

739
01:03:27.090 --> 01:03:29.260
Do you think me capable
of such naked deceit?

740
01:03:49.950 --> 01:03:52.290
What did he say. at the end?

741
01:03:55.290 --> 01:03:57.670
Did he speak my name?

742
01:04:17.770 --> 01:04:19.480
He was weary.

743
01:04:21.610 --> 01:04:24.480
It was hard. at
times. to understand.

744
01:04:26.440 --> 01:04:28.320
But he spoke Aegon's name.

745
01:04:36.450 --> 01:04:38.119
He said he was the
prince that was promised

746
01:04:38.120 --> 01:04:39.670
to unite the realm.

747
01:04:40.630 --> 01:04:42.459
- What?
- I desire peace as you do.

748
01:04:42.460 --> 01:04:45.459
- but if... - Did my
father use those words?

749
01:04:45.460 --> 01:04:46.969
The Prince That Was Promised?

750
01:04:49.470 --> 01:04:50.799
Did he?

751
01:04:50.800 --> 01:04:52.550
Yes. he did.

752
01:04:55.560 --> 01:04:59.639
He... spoke to you of
the Song of Ice and Fire?

753
01:05:06.530 --> 01:05:09.700
It's a story he once told...

754
01:05:10.360 --> 01:05:13.030
(chuckles) about
Aegon the Conqueror.

755
01:05:18.370 --> 01:05:20.540
The C... The Conqueror.

756
01:05:37.850 --> 01:05:39.679
You must go before
you are discovered.

757
01:05:39.680 --> 01:05:41.849
- There's been a mistake.
- There's been no mistake.

758
01:05:41.850 --> 01:05:42.900
Please.

759
01:05:44.610 --> 01:05:46.860
You can prevent this. Alicent.

760
01:05:48.280 --> 01:05:50.359
A terrible war is looming.

761
01:05:50.360 --> 01:05:51.909
and even victory
may be so bloody

762
01:05:51.910 --> 01:05:53.110
as to be counted a loss.

763
01:05:53.240 --> 01:05:57.740
- Do not let your pride blind...
- There's been no mistake.

764
01:06:01.120 --> 01:06:03.420
My father is gone from court.

765
01:06:04.580 --> 01:06:06.750
Cole is on the march. Aemond...

766
01:06:09.130 --> 01:06:11.050
you know what Aemond is.

767
01:06:17.470 --> 01:06:20.060
- It's too late. Rhaenyra.
- Alicent.

768
01:08:07.210 --> 01:08:09.460
<i>Only
weeks ago. my Lord husband was alive</i>

769
01:08:09.540 --> 01:08:10.669
and the realm was at peace.

770
01:08:13.710 --> 01:08:15.420
You might be half the
king your father was.

771
01:08:15.550 --> 01:08:17.220
- Tread carefully.
- Or what?

772
01:08:18.720 --> 01:08:21.050
All who refuse will
have their death.

773
01:08:24.390 --> 01:08:25.390
Are you afraid. sir?

774
01:08:25.520 --> 01:08:27.230
Worse. I'm rational.

775
01:08:29.400 --> 01:08:32.360
<i>My father believed
that I was meant to unite the realm.</i>

776
01:08:33.190 --> 01:08:35.240
<i>I need to know that
there was no other path.</i>

777
01:08:35.400 --> 01:08:36.400
<i>And now I do.</i>

778
01:08:36.900 --> 01:08:38.260
Hold to your courage!

779
01:08:39.410 --> 01:08:40.410
Hold to your wit!

780
01:08:40.530 --> 01:08:42.410
<i>We must send the dragons to war.</i>

781
01:08:44.740 --> 01:08:49.250
<i>The horrors I have just loosed
cannot be for a crown alone.</i>

782
01:08:58.010 --> 01:09:00.339
<i>For Rhaenyra.
it's a really outlandish risk</i>

783
01:09:00.340 --> 01:09:02.599
<i>to try and go to
Alicent and say.</i>

784
01:09:02.600 --> 01:09:05.719
<i>"We are the only two people
left at either of these councils</i>

785
01:09:05.720 --> 01:09:08.310
that have the power.
influence. and desire

786
01:09:08.440 --> 01:09:10.600
<i>to see about a peaceful
end to this thing.</i>

787
01:09:15.780 --> 01:09:18.950
Your false queen.
Rhaenyra. is a kinslayer.

788
01:09:19.610 --> 01:09:22.910
Your uncle declared
for Aegon. did he?

789
01:09:23.620 --> 01:09:27.660
Aegon Targaryen is no true king.

790
01:09:28.120 --> 01:09:31.620
The Brackens and the Blackwoods
are ancient foes and rivals.

791
01:09:31.960 --> 01:09:33.960
<i>One of the big ideas
about this series</i>

792
01:09:34.130 --> 01:09:35.840
was generational conflict.

793
01:09:37.460 --> 01:09:39.840
<i>That's the standing of the
Blackwoods and the Brackens</i>

794
01:09:39.970 --> 01:09:40.970
<i>when we first find them.</i>

795
01:09:41.130 --> 01:09:42.840
which is a sort of
microcosm of where

796
01:09:42.970 --> 01:09:44.510
<i>House Targaryen is getting to.</i>

797
01:09:47.100 --> 01:09:49.140
<i>They happen to
have the two largest armies</i>

798
01:09:49.270 --> 01:09:50.140
in the Riverlands.

799
01:09:50.270 --> 01:09:51.389
It's 40.000 swords

800
01:09:51.390 --> 01:09:53.310
if they all come together
under one banner.

801
01:09:53.610 --> 01:09:56.860
I will enlist the Brackens.
subdue the Riverlands.

802
01:09:57.360 --> 01:09:58.820
and take Harrenhal.

803
01:09:59.030 --> 01:10:00.109
A bold scheme indeed.

804
01:10:00.110 --> 01:10:01.319
Well. the gods favor the bold.

805
01:10:01.320 --> 01:10:02.609
They did not favor Ser Arryk.

806
01:10:03.620 --> 01:10:05.330
One of the pivotal scenes

807
01:10:05.490 --> 01:10:09.790
is the first day of
Cole's work as Hand.

808
01:10:10.120 --> 01:10:14.210
<i>We've always seen Cole
as a strong. brooding guy.</i>

809
01:10:14.460 --> 01:10:17.500
And this was a moment
to peel back all those layers

810
01:10:17.710 --> 01:10:20.840
and understand what he's
like alone in a room with himself.

811
01:10:21.170 --> 01:10:25.299
<i>It's such a
massively anxiety-inducing day for him</i>

812
01:10:25.300 --> 01:10:27.639
<i>because the Hand of the
King is a diplomat's role.</i>

813
01:10:27.640 --> 01:10:30.350
<i>and he's always been the
sworn protector to the Queen.</i>

814
01:10:30.520 --> 01:10:33.350
Now. that duty of care has
been passed on to someone else.

815
01:10:33.480 --> 01:10:35.230
and suddenly all
eyes are on him.

816
01:10:35.650 --> 01:10:37.860
<i>That's a very
nerve-wracking thing.</i>

817
01:10:40.860 --> 01:10:43.070
Cole is a terrible choice
to be Hand of the King.

818
01:10:43.200 --> 01:10:47.369
<i>Aegon's ultimate goal is to have
someone who is a feared warrior.</i>

819
01:10:47.370 --> 01:10:48.659
<i>but not a great politician.</i>

820
01:10:48.660 --> 01:10:50.540
because he doesn't
want to be outshone.

821
01:10:50.870 --> 01:10:51.870
To war. then.

822
01:10:53.250 --> 01:10:54.540
I'll come. too. with Sunfyre.

823
01:10:54.670 --> 01:10:55.999
- Aegon.
- Your Grace.

824
01:10:56.000 --> 01:10:58.550
Aegon has this insecurity

825
01:10:58.710 --> 01:11:02.220
that drives a great
sense of confidence.

826
01:11:02.760 --> 01:11:04.680
I'm as fearsome as any of them.

827
01:11:04.880 --> 01:11:07.849
In this case. he wants
to wear the King's armor.

828
01:11:07.850 --> 01:11:11.139
<i>He wants to visually
push himself forward</i>

829
01:11:11.140 --> 01:11:12.230
as a leader.

830
01:11:12.560 --> 01:11:14.480
<i>Aegon is not thinking tactically.</i>

831
01:11:14.560 --> 01:11:17.400
He's being impulsive. It's
the same old trends in him.

832
01:11:18.020 --> 01:11:21.900
His self-awareness is growing.
and not in a good way for him

833
01:11:22.030 --> 01:11:24.900
because he's becoming more
aware of how much of a fraud he is.

834
01:11:25.450 --> 01:11:27.780
<i>And it's eating him
from the inside out.</i>

835
01:11:34.410 --> 01:11:35.999
<i>Daemon. in
the most base of ways.</i>

836
01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:38.290
<i>has a fight with his
wife. gets in his car.</i>

837
01:11:38.420 --> 01:11:41.050
and runs off to
Harrenhal to conquer it.

838
01:11:42.380 --> 01:11:44.260
<i>Daemon has gone. in his wisdom.</i>

839
01:11:44.380 --> 01:11:46.090
<i>to try and make amends. I think.</i>

840
01:11:46.430 --> 01:11:48.259
We've got to go and
march on King's Landing.

841
01:11:48.260 --> 01:11:49.640
<i>We need an army.
and at the moment.</i>

842
01:11:49.760 --> 01:11:50.920
<i>we don't really have an army.</i>

843
01:11:51.100 --> 01:11:53.389
<i>Daemon is hoping to
meet some resistance there.</i>

844
01:11:53.390 --> 01:11:54.430
<i>He's looking for it.</i>

845
01:11:54.770 --> 01:11:56.389
But he's frustrated in
the fact that he can't find it

846
01:11:56.390 --> 01:11:58.940
because the castle
is so poorly occupied.

847
01:12:03.440 --> 01:12:05.450
I'm claiming Harrenhal.

848
01:12:06.110 --> 01:12:07.280
Apparently so.

849
01:12:07.820 --> 01:12:10.780
<i>Simon
Strong is Lyonel Strong's uncle.</i>

850
01:12:10.990 --> 01:12:15.289
He has no loyalty to his family
because he is a man of honor

851
01:12:15.290 --> 01:12:18.460
and believes that
Larys burned his family.

852
01:12:24.840 --> 01:12:27.300
<i>Daemon comes
in. a head of steam.</i>

853
01:12:27.510 --> 01:12:30.470
and all Ser Simon wants
to do is have peace.

854
01:12:35.640 --> 01:12:38.190
<i>The most interesting
part of the Harrenhal story</i>

855
01:12:38.310 --> 01:12:39.650
<i>is what it does to Daemon.</i>

856
01:12:39.980 --> 01:12:42.979
He starts to have
these hallucinations.

857
01:12:42.980 --> 01:12:43.820
these dreams.

858
01:12:43.980 --> 01:12:46.150
He's not sure what's
real and not real.

859
01:12:48.990 --> 01:12:51.489
<i>We know that
there is a magicality.</i>

860
01:12:51.490 --> 01:12:54.540
<i>and all of a sudden. he
sees young Rhaenyra.</i>

861
01:12:54.790 --> 01:12:56.330
<i>and she means something to him.</i>

862
01:12:56.450 --> 01:12:57.829
<i>She meant something at that age.</i>

863
01:12:57.830 --> 01:13:00.040
and it also told him
that it was a dream.

864
01:13:02.790 --> 01:13:06.630
His past is coming back to
haunt him in broad daylight.

865
01:13:06.800 --> 01:13:08.969
<i>The real idea was
to bring Daemon into contact</i>

866
01:13:08.970 --> 01:13:11.010
with something in
the supernatural world

867
01:13:11.140 --> 01:13:12.180
that he could not deny.

868
01:13:16.850 --> 01:13:18.400
I've decided to send Joffrey

869
01:13:18.480 --> 01:13:21.520
to ward with my cousin.
Lady Jeyne Arryn.

870
01:13:21.860 --> 01:13:23.860
Aegon and Viserys
will accompany him.

871
01:13:24.860 --> 01:13:26.190
I want you to go with them.

872
01:13:26.530 --> 01:13:28.109
<i>Rhaenyra's made
this immediate calculation</i>

873
01:13:28.110 --> 01:13:29.279
<i>that her family is unsafe.</i>

874
01:13:29.280 --> 01:13:30.659
<i>I mean. they got
to her in her home.</i>

875
01:13:30.660 --> 01:13:32.580
and there's nothing to
say that they can't again.

876
01:13:32.700 --> 01:13:34.060
<i>I think she sends
away her youngest</i>

877
01:13:34.200 --> 01:13:36.410
<i>and most vulnerable
children to protect them</i>

878
01:13:36.540 --> 01:13:37.920
<i>in a place where
they're hidden away</i>

879
01:13:38.000 --> 01:13:40.040
and hopefully where
they can weather the war.

880
01:13:40.540 --> 01:13:44.540
The endless risk of
losing one of your children.

881
01:13:44.710 --> 01:13:48.379
<i>I think she perceives to
be hideously compromising</i>

882
01:13:48.380 --> 01:13:50.550
<i>while she's in that
grieving process.</i>

883
01:13:50.720 --> 01:13:53.389
There's a decision to
try and dislocate herself

884
01:13:53.390 --> 01:13:54.680
from her own motherhood.

885
01:13:54.890 --> 01:13:56.650
I cannot
promise to make you happy.

886
01:13:57.060 --> 01:14:00.890
but I ask you. make
this sacrifice willingly.

887
01:14:01.440 --> 01:14:02.690
For all of us.

888
01:14:03.230 --> 01:14:04.020
Your Grace.

889
01:14:04.270 --> 01:14:06.730
I think being in a family
that has so much power

890
01:14:06.860 --> 01:14:09.570
and feeling so
powerless is heartbreaking

891
01:14:09.690 --> 01:14:11.700
<i>when you have
such a want to help.</i>

892
01:14:11.910 --> 01:14:14.740
It's like confirmation to Rhaena
of what she's always feared.

893
01:14:14.910 --> 01:14:16.510
that everyone just
thinks she's pathetic.

894
01:14:16.790 --> 01:14:17.960
<i>She's also the daughter</i>

895
01:14:18.040 --> 01:14:20.409
of Daemon Targaryen
and Laena Velaryon.

896
01:14:20.410 --> 01:14:22.000
and there's a fire
burning in her as well.

897
01:14:22.080 --> 01:14:24.169
<i>It's really lit by
that resentment</i>

898
01:14:24.170 --> 01:14:28.250
of being sent on this mission
she regards as a bit demeaning.

899
01:14:28.420 --> 01:14:29.880
You do a great service.

900
01:14:30.220 --> 01:14:32.679
and may yet find yourself
glad to be out of harm's way.

901
01:14:32.680 --> 01:14:33.800
Do not coddle me. Baela.

902
01:14:34.260 --> 01:14:36.760
- Grant me at least that dignity.
- I meant no insult.

903
01:14:37.100 --> 01:14:39.930
Rhaena's definitely got
some bitterness and jealousy

904
01:14:40.060 --> 01:14:40.810
towards Baela.

905
01:14:41.140 --> 01:14:43.100
<i>but I think she's also.
like. in awe of her.</i>

906
01:14:43.270 --> 01:14:45.400
<i>There's always gonna
be such love there.</i>

907
01:14:45.560 --> 01:14:47.150
Very classic for sisters.

908
01:14:47.570 --> 01:14:49.650
Should all come to ruin here.

909
01:14:50.610 --> 01:14:52.280
<i>you will bear our
hope for the future.</i>

910
01:14:52.490 --> 01:14:53.870
<i>She also sends
away the three eggs</i>

911
01:14:53.950 --> 01:14:57.660
<i>that Daemon discovered from
Syrax's clutch in season one</i>

912
01:14:57.780 --> 01:15:00.749
<i>and the egg of young
Viserys Targaryen</i>

913
01:15:00.750 --> 01:15:02.290
as an insurance policy.

914
01:15:02.410 --> 01:15:04.459
so that all of her
eggs are not in

915
01:15:04.460 --> 01:15:06.250
the singular Dragonstone basket.

916
01:15:06.630 --> 01:15:08.500
<i>hoping that while
Lady Jeyne Arryn wants</i>

917
01:15:08.630 --> 01:15:10.459
an adult dragon
to defend the Vale.

918
01:15:10.460 --> 01:15:12.470
<i>the sons of House Targaryen</i>

919
01:15:12.590 --> 01:15:15.299
<i>and multiple dragon
eggs will do the job.</i>

920
01:15:18.640 --> 01:15:19.850
What do you know
of the movements

921
01:15:19.930 --> 01:15:21.140
of Alicent Hightower?

922
01:15:21.470 --> 01:15:22.809
<i>Rhaenyra sees what's coming.</i>

923
01:15:22.810 --> 01:15:24.139
She's trying to put an end to it

924
01:15:24.140 --> 01:15:27.649
<i>and to beseech Alicent to
help her see that through.</i>

925
01:15:29.110 --> 01:15:30.980
<i>She sees it as her
job as Sovereign</i>

926
01:15:31.110 --> 01:15:33.700
to risk herself before
she risks the lives

927
01:15:33.820 --> 01:15:35.450
<i>of possibly millions
of the realm.</i>

928
01:15:35.860 --> 01:15:37.490
It's quite a chaotic choice.

929
01:15:37.660 --> 01:15:40.619
<i>but Rhaenyra also
wants to look the person</i>

930
01:15:40.620 --> 01:15:43.000
who's caused her
such pain in the face.

931
01:15:45.500 --> 01:15:48.040
- (GASPS. INHALES
SHAKILY) - Shh.

932
01:15:48.960 --> 01:15:51.839
When Rhaenyra and
Alicent come together.

933
01:15:51.840 --> 01:15:56.259
<i>they're right back to that
moment where Viserys died.</i>

934
01:15:56.260 --> 01:15:57.510
<i>He changed his mind.</i>

935
01:15:58.220 --> 01:16:00.850
I have been at times
unkind. but never untrue.

936
01:16:01.680 --> 01:16:03.139
She has to reckon
for the first time

937
01:16:03.140 --> 01:16:06.479
with the idea that possibly
her father changed his mind.

938
01:16:06.480 --> 01:16:08.520
<i>that she lost the mandate.</i>

939
01:16:08.860 --> 01:16:10.939
<i>But when Alicent explains</i>

940
01:16:10.940 --> 01:16:14.109
that his last wish was
that Aegon be king.

941
01:16:14.110 --> 01:16:17.200
and she starts talking about
the prince that was promised.

942
01:16:17.360 --> 01:16:19.700
that's when Rhaenyra realizes

943
01:16:19.870 --> 01:16:23.370
that Viserys was talking
about the prophecy.

944
01:16:23.870 --> 01:16:26.370
It's a story he once told...

945
01:16:27.750 --> 01:16:29.710
(CHUCKLES) ...about
Aegon the Conqueror.

946
01:16:30.710 --> 01:16:32.799
That story and what
she's told herself

947
01:16:32.800 --> 01:16:34.210
has given her such strength.

948
01:16:34.550 --> 01:16:39.760
This just throws Alicent's
world into complete chaos.

949
01:16:39.890 --> 01:16:42.009
- There has been a mistake.
- There has been no mistake.

950
01:16:42.010 --> 01:16:43.010
Please.

951
01:16:43.350 --> 01:16:46.559
Rulers can exploit prophecy.
either knowingly or unknowingly.

952
01:16:46.560 --> 01:16:48.060
to see through it their power

953
01:16:48.190 --> 01:16:49.730
and their influence
over the realm.

954
01:16:49.900 --> 01:16:51.560
A terrible war is looming.

955
01:16:52.020 --> 01:16:53.529
and even victory
may be so bloody

956
01:16:53.530 --> 01:16:54.730
as to be counted a loss.

957
01:16:54.900 --> 01:16:56.149
Do not let your pride blind you

958
01:16:56.150 --> 01:16:58.570
- to the blood... - There
has been no mistake.

959
01:16:59.360 --> 01:17:00.990
<i>Rhaenyra does
not get what she wants.</i>

960
01:17:01.070 --> 01:17:03.079
It's not because Alicent's
unwilling to hear it.

961
01:17:03.080 --> 01:17:04.740
It's simply because
Alicent is saying.

962
01:17:04.870 --> 01:17:06.200
"My power has
been stripped away."

963
01:17:06.620 --> 01:17:07.980
<i>Even if she wanted
to do something.</i>

964
01:17:08.250 --> 01:17:09.829
<i>she feels like her
hands are tied.</i>

965
01:17:09.830 --> 01:17:11.250
It's too late. Rhaenyra.

966
01:17:11.380 --> 01:17:12.380
Alicent.

967
01:17:14.750 --> 01:17:16.420
And that causes
her to have to reckon.

968
01:17:16.550 --> 01:17:17.920
finally. with going to war.

969
01:17:18.050 --> 01:17:20.930
<i>And suddenly. she
chooses her title.</i>

970
01:17:21.430 --> 01:17:22.550
She doesn't just inherit it.

971
01:17:22.930 --> 01:17:25.679
<i>Alicent and
Rhaenyra are both affected</i>

972
01:17:25.680 --> 01:17:27.889
by what they have lost

973
01:17:27.890 --> 01:17:29.940
<i>and the history that they have
with each other.</i>

974
01:17:30.060 --> 01:17:31.230
<i>You don't forget it.</i>

975
01:17:31.440 --> 01:17:35.440
<i>So. the rest of the season
is about embracing reality.</i>

976
01:17:35.520 --> 01:17:37.520
